  "notes": "Leprosy — annual, 5 'Annual' tabs via extra_sheets (Annual=Registered+NewlyDetected, Annual1=Confirmed, Annual2=Treated, Annual3=CompletedMDT, Annual4=G2D). Province/HUC granularity only, 4 real rows; NIR rollup (row 2) skipped via data_start_row:1. location_column:2 (col 1 is the 'NIRA' region literal, FLAG 10). ALL indicators is_sensitive=TRUE (stigma). Three source bugs FIXED here, not copied: Annual col-11 prevalence 0-14 missing its x10,000 (FLAG 1) — recomputed; Annual 'E.Total' (idx31) + CDR 15-18 (idx32) are a rate/double-rate not a Male+Female sum (FLAG 2) — recomputed as sum then rate; Annual2 all-ages %treated has a dangling #REF! (FLAG 3). %treated/%completed are NOT config-computed — their denominators (Confirmed totals) live cross-sheet in Annual1, which the parser's per-sheet row_values cannot reach; instead LEP_TREATED_*_PCT / LEP_COMPLETED_*_PCT are seeded with denominator_source=LEP_CONF_*_TOTAL and derived by the analytics/Coverage layer (health_data lookup is sheet-agnostic). Population repeated in 3 tabs (FLAG 8): Annual holds canonical LEP_POP_*; Annual4 has its own LEP_G2D_POP_* copy so its G2D rate resolves within-sheet without a duplicate-staging collision. Rates stored already-multiplied (ADR-023): prevalence x10,000, CDR x100,000, G2D x1,000,000. Registered all-ages M/F are independently entered raw (FLAG 4). Population for 15-18/19+ is blank in province rows (FLAG 7) so those age-specific rates resolve None — expected, a DOH data gap not a parser bug. Deferred DQC (need D4 sequence/reconciliation): Registered>=Confirmed>=Treated>=Completed; all-ages == sum of age groups; %treated/%completed <= 100%. Annual2/Annual3 have a trailing footnote row in the PSGC column (FLAG 5) — expected as ignorable annotation noise."
